race.comment: PETTICOAT (1) brings the strongest form lines here and Roper's 2kg claim keeps her in the contest. Won here two back in good style, before heading to Eagle Farm when a narrow on pace second over 1000m in BM78 grade. Gone to a new level this campaign and will take running down. FLYING IMPALA (4) blinkers go on for this and indicated he was near his best when a tough on-pace fourth over 1200m at Nowra. Comes back in trip and will have little trouble getting across from the wide draw. Expected to take a hand in the finish. MIC DROP (9) emerging country-trained mare who deserves her shot in town. Tough win up on the speed from the sticky draw when saluting over 1000m at Muswellbrook in easier grade. Keep safe. CHEMTRAIL (7) sent for a spell after disappointing in town over the 1200m at this level last May. Out of his depth on resumption when eighth to Roselyn's Star over 1100m at Rosehill in a BM78. Back in trip and class and maps well.
